  "texts": [
    "Third, we find that ChatGPT usage has grown relatively faster in low-and middle-income countries over the last year.",
    "Fourth, we find that educated users and users in highly-paid professional occupations are substantially more likely to use ChatGPT for work.",
    "We introduce a new taxonomy to classify messages according to the kind of output the user is seeking, using a simple rubric that we call Asking, Doing, or Expressing.",
    "11 Asking is when the user is seeking information or clarification to inform a decision, corresponding to problem-solving models of knowledge work (e.g., Garicano (2000); Garicano and Rossi-Hansberg (2006); Carnehl and Schneider (2025); Ide and Talamas (2025)).",
    "Doing is when the user wants to produce some output or perform a particular task, corresponding to classic task-based models of work (e.g., Autor et al. (2003))."
  ],
